{
  "texts": [
    "Another way to study the biases in LLM answers is to examine the groundtruth subpopulations that each LLM subpopulation's answers come closest to.",
    "In other words, to map each LLM subpopulation to its best-matching ground-truth subpopulation(s), and then examine the properties of these best matches.",
    "This can be achieved through a k-nearest-neighbor approach, where to each LLM subpopulation we assign the k ground-truth subpopulations that",
    "have the closest answer distributions.",
    "We report results for k = 10, where each LLM answer pattern in associated to its 10 closest WVS distributions."
  ]
}